node.text: Looking back it’s been a year we will never forget. We kept climbing and so did you. Here’s to a new journey and possibilities for all in 2021. Thank you Aspen Snowmass community for your continued support. We can’t wait to see you on the hill this winter! Let winter lift you up. ( 🎥 : @andycurtis55 )

node.text:
"The vibe is high." Recently, the crew at @freeskiermagazine came to Aspen to see what our ski season looks like this winter. We rallied a few of our athletes @rhianna_borderick @colterjh @whitboucher and staff @xxxanthe to show @freeskiermagazine what the hype is all about. 

While searching for the next best powder stashes across Aspen Mountain and Aspen Highlands, our team gave them an inside look at how we have adapted to the new normal this year. Things like contactless lift ticket pickup boxes, easy grab and go mobile app food ordering, a new look at aprés and more. While somethings have certainly changed this season, some things will always stay the same here at Aspen Snowmass: the top notch ski experience, the collective passion of our guests and community, and our dedication to always providing you the best mountain moments possible - no matter what. ( 🎥 : @tylerwr )

node.text: Today is Colorado Gives Day! Join us in supporting our two employee funded and led non-profits. The Caring for Community Fund empowers our employees to take care of our friends and neighbors throughout the Roaring Fork Valley. And our Environment Foundation is dedicated to protecting the regional environment by funding projects tackling climate change and bolstering clean energy. It’s simple, when we aren’t working, we are outside and in the community. To find out more and contribute, visit the link in our bio.

node.text: Looking for ways to do something meaningful and help shape your future? Here's a really easy one: fill out the 2020 Census. The federal census takes place every ten years. Its results determine how the government allocates billions of dollars to local communities, and it will redistribute congressional representation based on population changes. If you care about the place you live, you should view the census as a civic duty. It only takes ten minutes--shorter than a lift ride. So visit 2020census.gov and get yourself counted.

node.text:
The Voting Rights Act has a long history of overwhelming bipartisan support. Today, we must continue to protect the right for all eligible Americans to vote. To that end, we’ve joined with more than 160 companies to urge Congress to pass the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act (VRAA) to protect voters against discrimination.

“We are proud to live in Colorado, which had record voter turnout last year, and want to ensure folks across the country can participate in free and fair elections. So, we’d like to thank Senator Bennet for cosponsoring the John Lewis VRAA in the last Congress, which will prevent discrimination at the polls and ensure all Americans can easily vote.” -Mike Kaplan, CEO and President, Aspen Skiing Company. 

Learn more by following the link in our bio.
